data.name: Brian's Farming Videos
data.description:
Brian is a 4th generation farmer in southern Ohio who started this channel in 2018 with the intent to record and save memories from daily life and farm activities. It wasn't long before the channel evolved into primarily a farm vlogging channel as Brian discovered his passion for educating and sharing with people the daily ups and downs that farmers and their family's experience year to year. while this is mostly a farm channel from time to time we also post other things we enjoy doing such as hunting, hiking, and family activities.
 
Follow us on Instagram https://www.instagram.com/briansfarmingvideos/ 
and Facebook https://www.facebook.com/BrownFamilyFarms1929/

For business inquires contact us at Briansfarmingvideos@gmail.com

data.name: Stoney Ridge Farmer
data.description:
Welcome to the Stoney Ridge Farm where we share a slice of the good life! Farming, wrenching and building as well as prepping, cooking and canning, there's something for everyone here on the channel!

The Stoney Ridge Farm 150 acre farm nestled in the foothills of the Blue Ridge Mountains of North Carolina.  Most of my videos are practical videos of things that need to be done around a small farm to keep equipment and the farm up and running.


These "how to" and Vlog type videos are meant to be informative and entertaining tidbits of farm life here on the Stoney Ridge.

I hope you enjoy our videos, please subscribe to our page and Ill teach you everything I can about starting a farm from scratch.
As an Amazon Associate I earn from qualifying purchases.

data.description: A little bit of everything.

data.name: How Farms Work
data.description:
Remembering the lost part of America's rural history.

We're a YouTube channel dedicated to showing people who weren't born on a farm what the farming life is like by vlogging events on the farm from How To Operate videos, all the way down to daily activities.

How Farms Work is a dynamic family-friendly farm vlog that showcases several beef and crop farms located in Southwestern Wisconsin. Equipment operation, techniques, daily activities, and farming strategies are all first-hand accounts given by Ryan, an agricultural business major whose family run these farms. How Farms Work takes place on over 10 different farms, with each farm ranging from 30 to 200+ acres.
Be sure to subscribe to stay in touch with farming practices, new and old, used in the Midwest or if you are a farmer or aspiring farmer!

*SUMMER SCHEDULE*
Our schedule may vary, but expect a new video every Sunday at 11 AM CDT!

data.name: Khan Academy
data.description:
Khan Academy is a nonprofit providing a free, world-class education for anyone, anywhere. Our interactive practice problems, articles, and videos help students succeed in math, biology, chemistry, physics, history, economics, finance, grammar, and many other topics.

Khan Academy provides teachers with data on how their students are doing so they can identify gaps in learning and provide tailored instruction. We  also offer free personalized SAT and LSAT practice in partnership with the College Board and the Law School Admission Council. 

Our resources have been translated into dozens of languages, and 15 million people around the globe learn on Khan Academy each month.

Want to extend your learning beyond YouTube? Practice what you've just discovered for free: www.khanacademy.org

data.analysisText:
Partnership Potential: High, due to the channel's large audience and reputation as a trusted educational resource.

PROS:
1. Wide Reach: With over 8 million subscribers and over 2 billion views, partnering with Khan Academy can offer high visibility and extensive reach.
2. Trusted Source: As a reputable and established educational platform, a brand partnership can be seen as credible and trustworthy.
3. Diverse Audience: Content ranges from elementary school topics to college-level subjects, reaching a diverse demographic of students, parents, and educators.
4. Global Impact: The channel's resources are used globally and translated into multiple languages, providing international exposure.
5. Association with Education: Brands can be associated with positive values like education, knowledge, and social responsibility.

CONS:
1. Limited Commercial Focus: As a nonprofit educational organization, overtly commercial content may not align with their mission and could face backlash from the audience.
2. Brand Fit: Brands unrelated to education or self-improvement might not resonate well with the audience.
3. Content Integration: Integrating brand messages into educational content in a non-disruptive way could be challenging.
4. Limited Engagement: The nature of educational content may not drive as much audience engagement as entertainment-focused channels.
5. Less Frequent Purchasing Intent: Viewers come primarily for learning, not shopping, which may limit immediate conversion rates.

Best fit for:
1. EdTech Companies
2. Book Publishers
3. Office Supplies Brands
4. Financial Literacy or Student Loan Companies
5. Science & Tech Firms promoting STEM education.
